<p>President Trump commuted the federal prison sentence of former New York congressman George Santos on Friday, ordering his immediate release from custody in New Jersey [politico.com#1][dw.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. In a post on Truth Social, the President wished Santos well and said he acted because Santos had been held in solitary confinement and &quot;horribly mistreated&quot; [france24.com#1][politico.com#1]. Santos had pleaded guilty to fraud and identity theft charges and was sentenced in April to more than seven years; he had served less than three months before the commutation [politico.com#1][theguardian.com#1][france24.com#1]. His lawyer said Santos left FCI Fairton in New Jersey and was heading home shortly after the announcement [theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/cJ1cG9VK08MgriWPuGNRdrvxv0q-naOHCHl_1WQmWAcCqhOy1gKbtyrx46Kcqeo-nrvFODvqJkO_GZNGWHZF1pmbuP-0TV-KsC0A1QmBhbTfalBtUsm2WoUy_dIzLEjIbHfvD1d6r1CDSvljPWtwYeYxrPQOTDMIukIWieY' alt='President Trump announced on Truth Social that he commuted George Santos’ sentence and ordered his immediate release.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Offense details: Santos admitted using donor funds for personal gain, filing false FEC reports, and stealing the identities and financial data of elderly and cognitively impaired donors, while also deceiving contributors into giving to a sham group [politico.com#1].</li><li>Victim count: Court filings said he stole the identities of 11 people, including family members, during his campaign activity [scmp.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1].</li><li>Judge’s rebuke: At April sentencing, U.S. District Judge Joanna Seybert condemned Santos’ “flagrant thievery,” calling him “an arrogant fraudster talking out of both sides of his mouth” [politico.com#1].</li><li>Public fabrications: Earlier, Santos falsely claimed ties to New York University, Goldman Sachs, and Citigroup, and said his grandparents fled the Nazis; he also presented himself as Jewish during his campaign [thehindu.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1].</li><li>Time served: He served 84 days of an 87-month sentence before being released under the commutation [straitstimes.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Good luck George, have a great life! - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He said Santos was &quot;somewhat of a &#x27;rogue&#x27;&quot; who had been in solitary confinement for long stretches and &quot;horribly mistreated,&quot; justifying the commutation. (<a href='https://www.politico.com/news/2025/10/17/trump-clemency-george-santos-00614693'>Politico</a>)</li><li>Judge Joanna Seybert: At sentencing, she criticized Santos’ conduct as &quot;flagrant thievery&quot; and described him as &quot;an arrogant fraudster,&quot; underscoring the severity of the offenses. (<a href='https://www.politico.com/news/2025/10/17/trump-clemency-george-santos-00614693'>Politico</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/oct/17/trump-commuted-sentence-george-santos'>Trump says he has commuted sentence of George Santos in federal fraud case</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/290ee871-ef3d-4f35-8d4a-a153fc34e29b'>Trump commutes prison sentence of former Republican lawmaker George Santos</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/17/trump-commutes-sentence-of-former-republican-lawmaker-george-santos'>Trump commutes sentence of former Republican lawmaker George Santos</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/trump-commutes-sentence-of-disgraced-former-us-rep-george-santos-in-fraud-case/'>Trump commutes sentence of disgraced former US Rep. George Santos in fraud case</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/former-us-congressman-george-santos-released-from-prison-after-trump-commutes-his-7-year-sentence'>Former US congressman George Santos released from prison after Trump comm